# Pet Minder UI Design System
- Treat `pet-minder/design.md` as the source of truth for all UI work in this repo.
- Do not invent colours, spacing, layout patterns, or component patterns. Match the classes and structure from the design document.
- Typography: use `font-display` for headings, `text-muted-foreground` for subtitles, avoid `font-bold`, and never go below `text-xs`.
- Colour tokens: use `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `border-border`, `shadow-card`, and the provided `teal-*`/status classes exactly as defined.
- Icons: use `lucide-react` with the icon names and `size-*` classes specified in `pet-minder/design.md`.
- Live session UI: use the provided card structure, `animate-live-pulse`, and amber card glow classes as shown.
- Voice and tone: warm but direct, calm empty states, no emoji in functional UI.

